{{Infobox video game | developer = [[Davidson & Associates]] | publisher = Davidson & Associates | released = 1984 | platforms = [[Apple II]] }}
'''''Word Attack!''''' is a 1984 [[education]]al [[video game]] by [[Davidson & Associates]]. An updated version was released entitled ''Word Attack! Plus.'' The game found similar success to the Davidson titles ''[[Spell It]]'' and ''[[Reading and Me]].''
== Gameplay == The game consists of a series of language-based "[[drill-and-practice]]" [[minigame]]s and exercises. In one, the player uses the [[arrow keys]] to fire at correct answer "targets". The nine programs are aimed at grades 4-12.
== Commercial performance == By October 13, 1984, the game had sustained an 11-week streak on the [[Billboard charts|Billboard Charts]] for Top Educational Computer Software.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=MiQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT26&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjP3KSeuPjRAhWE2LwKHXE0BBI4ChDoAQg4MAg#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-10-13|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> It re-entered the charts on November 3, 1984 at #9,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=wCQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA31&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiU8PSXuPjRAhVDULwKHSqYAswQ6AEIJTAD#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-11-03|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> and again on November 24, 1984 at #7.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=nyQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA25&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwizo66kuPjRAhXIXbwKHYSyDso4FBDoAQgoMAQ#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1984-11-24|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref> By June 15, 1985, the game had stayed on the list for a total of 44 weeks, and was currently at #8.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=-SQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT28&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiU8PSXuPjRAhVDULwKHSqYAswQ6AEIOTAI#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1985-06-15|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>
== Critical reception == ''The Computer in Reading and Language Arts'' criticised the [[Game mechanics|mechanic]] of shooting the correct [[multiple choice]] answers, deeming the [[graphics]] to be out of place in an educational title.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=CYZ4__pBowgC&pg=PA22&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjP3KSeuPjRAhWE2LwKHXE0BBI4ChDoAQgYMAA#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=The Computer in Reading and Language Arts|last=Blanchard|first=Jay S.|last2=Mason|first2=George E.|date=1987-01-01|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=9780866566674|language=en}}</ref> ''[[InfoWorld]]'' deemed it well-[[Organization|organised]] and flexible, adding that it is an [[Effectiveness|effective]] teaching tool.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=ri8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA60&dq=%22word+attack%22+davidsons+and+associates&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwizo66kuPjRAhXIXbwKHYSyDso4FBDoAQggMAI#v=onepage&q=%22word%20attack%22%20davidsons%20and%20associates&f=false|title=InfoWorld|last=Inc|first=InfoWorld Media Group|date=1983-10-17|publisher=InfoWorld Media Group, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>
